<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF286A97FD15940E1D6EBF33" pageId="211" pageNumber="973" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF286A97FD15940E1D6EBF33" blockId="211.[744,1337,441,868]" lastBlockId="211.[124,1336,879,2959]" pageId="211" pageNumber="973">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FC73940E1DE3B94A" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[911,995,599,632]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="973" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FBF5940E1ABAB94A" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1033,1210,599,632]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="973" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrodactylus">macrodactylus</taxonomicName>
species group (4 species). 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FBFE94271AA7B9AD" authorityName="Hollister" authorityYear="1912" box="[1026,1191,638,671]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="973" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petax">Myotis petax</taxonomicName>
has been considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FB9594F71B31B9F5" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[1129,1329,686,711]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="973" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="daubentonii">M. daubentonii</taxonomicName>
, but molecular and morphological data support its recognition as a distinct species. Genetic data indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FB3D95451B39B80F" authorityName="Hollister" authorityYear="1912" box="[1217,1337,796,829]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petax">M. petax</taxonomicName>
is closer to other East Asian 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FB6A951A1AEAB856" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1174,1258,835,868]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="973" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FF7E95361F0AB8BE" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[130,266,879,908]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pilosus">M. pilosus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FEE295361FD0B8BE" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[286,464,879,908]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fimbriatus">M. fimbriatus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FDDA95361D11B8BE" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[550,785,879,908]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrodactylus">M. macrodactylus</taxonomicName>
). Taxon abei has been recognized as a distinct species, butit is a junior synonym of nominate 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF286A97FC5795CB1DF0B881" authorityName="Hollister" authorityYear="1912" box="[939,1008,914,947]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="211" pageNumber="973" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petax">petax</taxonomicName>
based on morphology and molecular data. Subspecies loukashkini tentatively includes chasanensis, pending additional comparison. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
